            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="559" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Council/12–1345: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Truman</persName> to General
                            <persName type="to">Marshall</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-15">December 15,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">General Marshall</hi>: On your departure for China I wish
                    to send you this last word of encouragement and appreciation. I believe that the
                    development of a strong, united and democratic China is essential. The
                    alternatives seem to me clearly to be disunity or prolonged civil war, neither
                    of which would be in our interests nor in the interests of international peace.
                    I know that the problems involved are not easy ones but I am confident that you
                    will be able to solve them with complete success.</p>
                <p>You carry with you as you enter upon the task ahead of you my full support and
                    complete confidence.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harry</hi> S. <hi rend="smallcaps">Truman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
